# Line-ending normalization.
#
# The repo is developed on a mix of Windows and Linux. core.autocrlf
# is set to `false` for this clone, which means whatever bytes are in
# a file at commit time are the bytes that end up in the git blob. For
# most files that is fine (Go is line-ending-agnostic), but shell
# scripts with a `\r` in the shebang line break on Linux:
#
#     /usr/bin/env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory
#
# ...which silently kills CI jobs. Forcing `*.sh` to LF at the blob
# level fixes this regardless of the contributor's local autocrlf
# setting, without forcing any change on working copies that are
# already LF.
#
# `*.py` gets the same treatment because our deploy scripts run on
# the VPS (Linux) and we ran into the same permission-denied class of
# bugs when Windows-created `.py` files were rsynced over.

*.sh      text eol=lf
*.py      text eol=lf
*.yml     text eol=lf
*.yaml    text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf

# Landing-site assets are LF on the wire — they are deployed to the
# Caddy host at /var/www/QSD via `cat > <remote>` (see
# cmd/QSD-deploy-landing) and the SRI hashes in wallet.html are
# computed by QSD/scripts/build_wallet_wasm.sh against LF content.
# A CRLF copy in the working tree would (a) make the SRI integrity
# check fail when served from a local dev server and (b) confuse the
# refresh script's sed-based hash injection. Forcing LF at the blob
# level keeps the working tree consistent with the deployed bytes.
#
# Per-extension targeting (not a directory-wide glob) so that
# wallet.wasm and other binary deploy artefacts are NOT touched by
# eol normalization — `text eol=lf` would mangle a binary file by
# stripping any 0x0D byte that happens to follow a 0x0A.
QSD/deploy/landing/*.html text eol=lf
QSD/deploy/landing/*.js   text eol=lf
QSD/deploy/landing/*.css  text eol=lf
QSD/deploy/landing/*.svg  text eol=lf
QSD/deploy/landing/*.wasm binary

# A subset of historical Go and repository metadata files use CRLF in the
# canonical blobs. Treat the carriage return as part of the line ending while
# still detecting real trailing spaces and tabs.
*.go       whitespace=cr-at-eol
*.ps1      whitespace=cr-at-eol
.gitignore whitespace=cr-at-eol

# Historical documentation and web/config assets contain a mix of canonical LF
# and CRLF blobs. Ignore only the CR byte at line endings while continuing to
# report actual trailing spaces and tabs. Explicit eol=lf rules above still
# control deployed landing assets and scripts.
*.md       whitespace=cr-at-eol
*.html     whitespace=cr-at-eol
*.js       whitespace=cr-at-eol
*.css      whitespace=cr-at-eol
*.xml      whitespace=cr-at-eol
*.txt      whitespace=cr-at-eol
QSD/deploy/Caddyfile whitespace=cr-at-eol

# Unified patches encode context lines with a leading marker; checking those
# markers as source indentation produces false positives in `git diff --check`.
*.patch -whitespace
